----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Model covers REQ-ATC-01 with structural invariants, safety assertions, and acceptance criteria reachability.
-- Summary 2: Edge case assertions check behavior when alternatives are unavailable or channels are unauthenticated.
-- Summary 3: Non-functional requirements are proxied via facts and assertions.
-- Assumption 1: Resource 'accessible' set models authorization; no explicit flight or runway sigs are defined.
-- Assumption 2: State transitions are abstract; Pre1/Post1/Post2 represent system states without detailed internal structure.
-- Assumption 3: NFRs are approximated by structural constraints (e.g., channel count, target size).
-- Open issue 1: Edge case assertions ec_safe_1 and ec_safe_2 may conflict with inv_state_must_change (op.pre != op.post) when no alternative exists, potentially making them unsatisfiable.
-- Open issue 2: The model lacks explicit flight and runway entities; acceptance criteria are modeled indirectly via resources and channels.
-- Open issue 3: Some predicates (e.g., tc_02_holds) use 'UI in op.channel.kind' but channel.kind is an IfaceKind, not a set; this is a type error that may cause analysis issues.


